hat moves our AIs toward fable-5 efficiency, from the fable-mode and opus-fable-mode sources\n31: \n32: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 3 -->\n33: <!--\n34: SELF-CHECK:\n35: - Confirm the plan names the simplest viable approach, affected surfaces, and verification path.\n36: - Match phases to the stated scope; remove setup theater that does not change the outcome.\n37: FAILURE MODES:\n38: - Over-planning, missing rollback, and treating assumptions as dependencies.\n39: -->\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n44: ## 1. SUMMARY\n45: \n46: ### Technical Context\n47: \n48: | Aspect | Value |\n49: |--------|-------|\n50: | **Language/Stack** | [e.g., TypeScript, Python 3.11] |\n51: | **Framework** | [e.g., React, FastAPI] |\n52: | **Storage** | [e.g., PostgreSQL, None] |\n53: | **Testing** | [e.g., Jest, pytest] |\n54: \n55: ### Overview\n56: [2-3 sentences: what this implements and the technical approach]\n57: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n62: ## 2. QUALITY GATES\n63: \n64: ### Definition of Ready\n65: - [ ] Problem statement clear and scope documented\n66: - [ ] Success criteria measurable\n67: - [ ] Dependencies identified\n68: \n69: ### Definition of Done\n70: - [ ] All acceptance criteria met\n71: - [ ] Tests passing (if applicable)\n72: - [ ] Docs updated (spec/plan/tasks)\n73: <!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: <!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n78: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n79: \n80: ### Pattern\n81: [MVC | MVVM | Clean Architecture | Serverless | Monolith | Other]\n82: \n83: ### Key Components\n84: - **[Component 1]**: [Purpose]\n85: - **[Component 2]**: [Purpose]\n86: \n87: ### Data Flow\n88: [Brief description of how data moves through the system]\n89: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: <!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n94: ## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES\n95: \n96: Use this section when `research_intent=fix_bug`, when planning from a deep-review FAIL/CONDITIONAL verdict, or when any finding touches security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, public responses, or shared policy.\n97: \n98: | Surface | Current Role | Action | Verification |\n99: |---------|--------------|--------|--------------|\n100: | [producer/helper/policy] | [what owns the behavior] | [update/unchanged/not a consumer] | [grep/test/doc evidence] |\n101: | [consumer/status/docs/tests] | [how it observes the behavior] | [update/unchanged/not a consumer] | [grep/test/doc evidence] |\n102: \n103: Required inventories:\n104: - Same-class producers: `rg -n '<field|string|helper|literal|error-pattern>' <module-or-files>`.\n105: - Consumers of changed symbols: `rg -n '<changedSymbol>|<changedConstant>|<changedPublicField>' . --glob '*.ts' --glob '*.js' --glob '*.md'`.\n106: - Matrix axes: list every independent input axis and the required rows before implementation.\n107: - Algorithm invariant: for path/redaction/parser/resolver/security fixes, state the invariant and adversarial cases.\n108: <!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n113: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n114: \n115: ### Phase 1: Setup\n116: - [ ] Project structure created\n117: - [ ] Dependencies installed\n118: - [ ] Development environment ready\n119: \n120: ### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n121: - [ ] [Core feature 1]\n122: - [ ] [Core feature 2]\n123: - [ ] [Core feature 3]\n124: \n125: ### Phase 3: Verification\n126: - [ ] Manual testing complete\n127: - [ ] Edge cases handled\n128: - [ ] Documentation updated\n129: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n134: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n135: \n136: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n137: |-----------|-------|-------|\n138: | Unit | [Components/functions] | [Jest/pytest/etc.] |\n139: | Integration | [API endpoints/flows] | [Tools] |\n140: | Manual | [User journeys] | Browser |\n141: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: <!-- ANCHOR