{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781518882878,"sessionID":"ses_13537258affeqeTEqC63wDuxy2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_66e4bee4f890471fa02ac009","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"## What Worked\n- grep for UserPromptSubmit across .opencode revealed the full cross-runtime hook architecture (iteration 1)\n- Reading the skill_advisor_hook.md reference directly clarified the OpenCode plugin bridge mechanism\n- Glob of constitutional memories + agent prompts revealed the full surface count (iteration 2)\n- grep for renderPromptPack/post-dispatch-validate in deep-loop-runtime found enforcement surfaces (iteration 2)\n\n## What Failed\n(none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\nImplementation path analysis: how would the top recommendations actually be implemented? Focus on the minimal viable change for (a) governor-in-agent-prompts, (b) governor-in-executor-config, (c) behavioral gates in post-dispatch-validate, and (d) the AGENTS.md dead pointer fix. Estimate blast radius for each.","oldString":"## What Worked\n- grep for UserPromptSubmit across .opencode revealed the full cross-runtime hook architecture (iteration 1)\n- Reading the skill_advisor_hook.md reference directly clarified the OpenCode plugin bridge mechanism\n\n## What Failed\n(none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\nSurface map gaps: which adjustable surfaces did the prior lineages miss? Focus on agent prompts (12 agents × 3 mirrors), constitutional memories (16+), deep-loop runtime integration points (renderPromptPack, post-dispatch-validate, executor-config), and the skill-advisor scoring/triggers surface."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -29,14 +29,16 @@\n \n ## What Worked\n - grep for UserPromptSubmit across .opencode revealed the full cross-runtime hook architecture (iteration 1)\n - Reading the skill_advisor_hook.md reference directly clarified the OpenCode plugin bridge mechanism\n+- Glob of constitutional memories + agent prompts revealed the full surface count (iteration 2)\n+- grep for renderPromptPack/post-dispatch-validate in deep-loop-runtime found enforcement surfaces (iteration 2)\n \n ## What Failed\n (none yet)\n \n ## Next Focus\n-Surface map gaps: which adjustable surfaces did the prior lineages miss? Focus on agent prompts (12 agents × 3 mirrors), constitutional memories (16+), deep-loop runtime integration points (renderPromptPack, post-dispatch-validate, executor-config), and the skill-advisor scoring/triggers surface.\n+Implementation path analysis: how would the top recommendations actually be implemented? Focus on the minimal viable change for (a) governor-in-agent-prompts, (b) governor-in-executor-config, (c) behavioral gates in post-dispatch-validate, and (d) the AGENTS.md dead pointer fix. Estimate blast radius for each.\n \n ## Active Risks\n - mimo-v2.5-pro may have lower capability ceiling than the prior lineages' models\n - Cross-runtime hook wiring data is sparse (only Claude hook was verified)\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -29,14 +29,16 @@\n \n ## What Worked\n - grep for UserPromptSubmit across .opencode revealed the full cross-runtime hook architecture (iteration 1)\n - Reading the skill_advisor_hook.md reference directly clarified the OpenCode plugin bridge mechanism\n+- Glob of constitutional memories + agent prompts revealed the full surface count (iteration 2)\n+- grep for renderPromptPack/post-dispatch-validate in deep-loop-runtime found enforcement surfaces (iteration 2)\n \n ## What Failed\n (none yet)\n \n ## Next Focus\n-Surface map gaps: which adjustable surfaces did the prior lineages miss? Focus on agent prompts (12 agents × 3 mirrors), constitutional memories (16+), deep-loop runtime integration points (renderPromptPack, post-dispatch-validate, executor-config), and the skill-advisor scoring/triggers surface.\n+Implementation path analysis: how would the top recommendations actually be implemented? Focus on the minimal viable change for (a) governor-in-agent-prompts, (b) governor-in-executor-config, (c) behavioral gates in post-dispatch-validate, and (d) the AGENTS.md dead pointer fix. Estimate blast radius for each.\n \n ## Active Risks\n - mimo-v2.5-pro may have lower capability ceiling than the prior lineages' models\n - Cross-runtime hook wiring data is sparse (only Claude hook was verified)\n","additions":3,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781518882874,"end":1781518882876}},"id":"prt_ecaccd8330010AmoixVbtVi4lg","sessionID":"ses_13537258affeqeTEqC63wDuxy2","messageID":"msg_ecaccb58a001dWelI33yVkBTAS"}}
